1
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:10,478
⟨I have spent days full of love with 50 people who love me →

2
00:00:10,544 --> 00:00:12,980
Detective Manami Tanizaki⟩

3
00:00:13,047 --> 00:00:16,984
⟨Ai-chan, a serial killer who made many sacrifices→

4
00:00:17,051 --> 00:00:19,487
I have continued the fight to pursue ⟩

5
00:00:19,553 --> 00:00:22,056
⟨Finally Manami...⟩

6
00:00:23,557 --> 00:00:26,994
⟨Finding the identity of the real culprit⟩

7
00:00:27,061 --> 00:00:31,999
⟨Manami, be yourself until the end⟩

8
00:00:32,066 --> 00:00:41,509
♪～

9
00:00:41,575 --> 00:00:44,011
(Manami) What are you doing?

10
00:00:44,078 --> 00:00:49,016
(Yuriko) What, Ai-chan, you came to catch me?

11
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:53,521
(Emoto) [Looks like Detective Kuroiwa's consciousness has returned]

12
00:00:53,587 --> 00:00:56,524
(Yuriko's voice) Kuroiwa-kun, your consciousness has returned, hasn't it?

13
00:00:56,590 --> 00:01:01,028
He might come to attack me... That's right, Ai-chan.

14
00:01:01,095 --> 00:01:03,964
(Manami) Yuriko: That information...｡

15
00:01:04,031 --> 00:01:06,467
>> Is Manami-chan waiting here?

16
00:01:06,534 --> 00:01:08,969
I guess I'll take a look.

17
00:01:09,036 --> 00:01:23,517
♪～

18
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:28,022
(Manami) Kamiki Clinic will be closed →

19
00:01:28,089 --> 00:01:32,026
A hidden safe was found in the director's room.

20
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:34,528
(Manami's voice) Among them →

21
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:37,531
There was Yuriko's medical record.

22
00:01:37,598 --> 00:01:42,036
>> Do you think I'm Ai-chan?

23
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:47,041
(Manami) She's my daughter, right? Her name is Ai-chan.

24
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:50,044
Manami Ono.

25
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:53,047
Same name as me.

26
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:57,051
Write “beautiful” in “love” →

27
00:01:57,117 --> 00:02:01,121
Her nickname is "Ai-chan."

28
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:07,995
>> Eh...｡

29
00:02:08,062 --> 00:02:12,132
My daughter's nickname is "Ai-chan" so I call her Ai-chan →

30
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,135
It's really violent.

31
00:02:14,201 --> 00:02:17,137
(Kiryu) You dropped this.

32
00:02:17,204 --> 00:02:20,141
When he attacked me at the temple.

33
00:02:20,207 --> 00:02:22,710
(Manami) This is →

34
00:02:22,776 --> 00:02:25,713
It's a keepsake.

35
00:02:25,779 --> 00:02:30,284
Manami passed away 15 years ago.

36
00:02:33,787 --> 00:02:36,724
>> You looked into it, right?

37
00:02:36,790 --> 00:02:41,795
Manami is one of the lovers who were killed.

38
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:47,234
[I'm dating several people at the same time →

39
00:02:47,301 --> 00:02:51,739
Being followed by one person]

40
00:02:51,805 --> 00:02:56,310
[“Don’t play around too much” etc.]

41
00:02:57,811 --> 00:03:02,249
[I was quite busy baking it →

42
00:03:02,316 --> 00:03:09,256
"I'll make my own decisions, so leave me alone."

43
00:03:13,761 --> 00:03:16,697
[But→

44
00:03:16,764 --> 00:03:20,201
Being followed →

45
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:22,770
Don't you say that normally? ]

46
00:03:24,271 --> 00:03:28,709
[No, but→

47
00:03:28,776 --> 00:03:33,714
I'll protect you even if you don't tell me →

48
00:03:33,781 --> 00:03:35,783
Parents?]

49
00:03:38,285 --> 00:03:42,289
(Kamiki) [Don't blame yourself...]

50
00:03:44,291 --> 00:03:47,227
[Whatever you say→

51
00:03:47,294 --> 00:03:51,298
It's too late... right?]

52
00:03:53,801 --> 00:03:55,235
[My love? ]

53
00:03:55,302 --> 00:03:58,739
(Yuriko's voice) 5 years ago Manami and I are dating a lot of people→

54
00:03:58,806 --> 00:04:02,743
I thought it was fate that we became friends.

55
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:05,679
(Manami) [Taking turns with 50 people...] >> [No]

56
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:08,182
(Iori) [Look!]

57
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:12,686
[I'm happier being tied to one person...]

58
00:04:12,753 --> 00:04:15,189
(Manami) [I'll decide that]

59
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,257
[It's my happiness]

60
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:24,264
>> [Aha... I'm sorry, was I bothering you?]

61
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:36,210
[Uh... Wow! Ugh! ]

62
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:38,712
[piercing sound]

63
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:42,716
(Yuriko's voice) When the man who was stalking Manami died →

64
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:44,718
I was convinced.

65
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:49,223
The only thing that kept me from dying this far was Manami→

66
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:52,793
It was to protect Manami-chan.

67
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:00,734
(Yuriko) Love is violence!

68
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,170
With a face like “I love you so I can’t help it” →

69
00:05:03,237 --> 00:05:05,673
It starts to hurt the other person.

70
00:05:05,739 --> 00:05:11,679
Tell, tie, shake, punch, kick, follow.

71
00:05:11,745 --> 00:05:15,249
Finally...I'll kill you.

72
00:05:17,251 --> 00:05:19,186
(Manami) That's so...

73
00:05:19,253 --> 00:05:21,689
>> Protecting Manami from love →

74
00:05:21,755 --> 00:05:24,191
It's the meaning of my life.

75
00:05:24,258 --> 00:05:27,761
(Manami) So what about everyone?

76
00:05:30,764 --> 00:05:33,701
>> Things went well at first.

77
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:38,205
But the plan gradually went awry →

78
00:05:38,272 --> 00:05:40,708
It was known to Kamiki.

79
00:05:40,774 --> 00:05:44,211
[That's all]

80
00:05:44,278 --> 00:05:46,714
[What do you mean "so far"? ]

81
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:49,216
[This is →

82
00:05:49,283 --> 00:05:53,721
I think it's time to end my life.

83
00:05:53,787 --> 00:05:57,224
[It was originally closed 15 years ago]

84
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:59,793
[Please do not close on your own! ]

85
00:06:02,296 --> 00:06:07,735
[Is there a problem if Manami-san can love just one person?] ]

86
00:06:09,737 --> 00:06:12,172
[The one person she doesn't have to worry about getting hurt...]

87
00:06:12,239 --> 00:06:15,676
[Because that is difficult→

88
00:06:15,743 --> 00:06:19,179
This is what happens]

89
00:06:19,246 --> 00:06:24,752
[Would you leave it to me? ]

90
00:06:27,254 --> 00:06:33,260
[Just like you want to help Manami-san...]

91
00:06:35,262 --> 00:06:38,699
(Kamiki) [Me too→

92
00:06:38,766 --> 00:06:41,769
I want to help you

93
00:06:43,771 --> 00:06:46,206
(Yuriko) You're being too conceited.

94
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:48,709
Kamiki says there's no need to worry about hurting Manami-chan.

95
00:06:48,776 --> 00:06:51,712
How can I say this?

96
00:06:51,779 --> 00:06:56,283
(Manami) Wasn't it important? About Yuriko.

97
00:07:01,288 --> 00:07:03,157
>> [Sound of stabbing] (Kamiki) [Ugh...]

98
00:07:03,223 --> 00:07:05,159
[Damn…]

99
00:07:05,225 --> 00:07:08,662
〔sorry…〕

100
00:07:08,729 --> 00:07:11,165
[I can't do anything...]

101
00:07:11,231 --> 00:07:14,168
[That's why it hurts!] ]

102
00:07:14,234 --> 00:07:17,671
[Uu… uh…]

103
00:07:17,738 --> 00:07:22,743
(Kiryu) After that, you tried to blame me and kill me?

104
00:07:24,244 --> 00:07:29,183
Because it's also Kiryu-kun's fault.

105
00:07:29,249 --> 00:07:32,252
Leave Manami-chan alone.

106
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:37,691
He even took away Aimi's memento.

107
00:07:37,758 --> 00:07:40,260
Because of that, even Kuroiwa-kun.

108
00:07:41,762 --> 00:07:45,265
(Kuroiwa) [I received this from Mr. Kiryu]

109
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:49,203
>> [Mobile phone? ]

110
00:07:49,269 --> 00:07:53,207
(Kuroiwa) [What are you doing, Yuriko-san]

111
00:07:53,273 --> 00:07:56,210
>> [If things continue like this, everyone will be happy →

112
00:07:56,276 --> 00:07:58,712
Kuroiwa-kun too]

113
00:07:58,779 --> 00:08:01,215
(Kuroiwa) [What are you talking about?]

114
00:08:01,281 --> 00:08:04,651
>> [Kiryu-kun was the culprit, so it was cleared up →

115
00:08:04,718 --> 00:08:08,155
Kiryu-kun is living his life hiding somewhere.]

116
00:08:08,222 --> 00:08:11,158
[Manami-chan took this opportunity to change her way of life]

117
00:08:11,225 --> 00:08:13,660
[Maybe someday→

118
00:08:13,727 --> 00:08:16,663
Only about Kuroiwa-kun, who is always by my side →

119
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:18,732
Maybe you'll love me

120
00:08:21,735 --> 00:08:24,171
[I told you so]

121
00:08:24,238 --> 00:08:26,673
[Kuroiwa-kun and Manami-chan→

122
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:30,244
I think it will go surprisingly well.]

123
00:08:35,249 --> 00:08:40,187
(Kuroiwa) [I'll decide that for you]

124
00:08:40,254 --> 00:08:42,256
>> [Eh? ]

125
00:08:44,258 --> 00:08:47,194
(Kuroiwa) [If Manami can't live like Manami →

126
00:08:47,261 --> 00:08:49,196
It makes no sense]

127
00:08:49,263 --> 00:08:51,265
>> [Ha…]

128
00:08:52,766 --> 00:08:55,702
[Why...]

129
00:08:55,769 --> 00:08:59,206
[Why don't you understand? ]

130
00:08:59,273 --> 00:09:03,710
(Kuroiwa) [Please, please turn yourself in]

131
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:07,648
>> [Hmm! ] (Kuroiwa) [Ah…]

132
00:09:07,714 --> 00:09:10,150
[Ah! Ugh...]

133
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:14,154
>> [Give me back my phone...]

134
00:09:14,221 --> 00:09:17,658
[Ah ha! Ha ha…]

135
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:19,726
[click]

136
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:27,668
[What!? Ha ha ha ha...]

137
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:31,738
[Ha! Ha ha ha ha…〕

138
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,242
[Sound of falling]

139
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,746
[Kuroiwa-kun…]

140
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:46,186
I am Aimi...

141
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:49,756
Manami-chan is important to me so I can't help it.

142
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:55,696
(Manami) Sorry, can you please go ahead?

143
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:59,266
>> Huh? (Manami) I want to talk with you.

144
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:12,012
(Manami) Yuriko is important, not me.

145
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:19,953
(Manami) Manami-san and I are different.

146
00:10:20,587 --> 00:10:23,023
It's obvious though.

147
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:25,025
(Yuriko) I understand.

148
00:10:25,092 --> 00:10:29,029
But I want to protect both of them.

149
00:10:29,096 --> 00:10:34,468
(Manami) Did Manami want to be protected?

150
00:10:34,534 --> 00:10:36,470
>> Huh?

151
00:10:36,536 --> 00:10:42,042
(Manami) Have you read Manami's case report?

152
00:10:44,544 --> 00:10:47,481
>>The criminal's statement is completely blank.

153
00:10:47,547 --> 00:10:50,484
(Manami) The culprit who snuck into the house is →

154
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:54,054
He also tried to kill Yuriko.

155
00:10:55,555 --> 00:10:57,991
>> Huh?

156
00:10:58,058 --> 00:11:00,494
(Manami) After Manami was stabbed→

157
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:06,500
I desperately tried to stop the culprit from heading to Yuriko's room.

158
00:11:06,566 --> 00:11:09,503
No matter how many times I get stung, I chase after you →

159
00:11:09,569 --> 00:11:12,572
"Just leave it to your mother," she said.

160
00:11:15,075 --> 00:11:18,578
>> That's a lie... That's...

161
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:23,517
(Manami) Inside the happiness I want to protect→

162
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:26,586
I think Yuriko was in there too.

163
00:11:28,588 --> 00:11:31,525
I don't know but...

164
00:11:31,591 --> 00:11:34,528
Because I'm not Aimi.

165
00:11:41,535 --> 00:11:44,037
(Manami) I just…｡

166
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:52,479
(Manami) It's true~ What can you do for me?

167
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:57,484
Hey, you understand.

168
00:11:57,551 --> 00:12:01,488
The feeling of losing someone important to you.

169
00:12:01,555 --> 00:12:03,990
I regret not being able to protect you →

170
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:08,995
It feels like your mind and body are being torn to shreds.

171
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:11,498
Hey, you understand, right?

172
00:12:11,565 --> 00:12:14,568
Why are you doing that?

173
00:12:16,570 --> 00:12:19,072
>>That's...

174
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:26,012
(Manami) Still, I managed to sew it together →

175
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:29,516
I got up desperately.

176
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:32,519
Over and over again.

177
00:12:32,586 --> 00:12:35,021
Why do you think that is?

178
00:12:37,023 --> 00:12:41,027
>> To fall in love again?

179
00:12:43,029 --> 00:12:45,966
(Manami) That's not all.

180
00:12:46,032 --> 00:12:48,969
That's not all.

181
00:12:49,035 --> 00:12:50,971
(Sound of sipping)

182
00:12:51,037 --> 00:12:53,974
It's for pot!

183
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:58,044
Iori and Yuriko.

184
00:13:00,046 --> 00:13:05,986
Really... the worst.

185
00:13:06,052 --> 00:13:07,988
(Sound of sipping)

186
00:13:08,054 --> 00:13:11,491
Weren't you cooking the pot all the time?

187
00:13:11,558 --> 00:13:13,994
(cry)

188
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:17,497
it was….

189
00:13:17,564 --> 00:13:21,001
Why did this happen?

190
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:36,449
♪～

191
00:13:36,516 --> 00:13:41,454
(sound of handcuffs being applied)

192
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:47,460
♪～

193
00:13:47,527 --> 00:13:54,968
(cry)

194
00:13:55,035 --> 00:13:59,973
♪～

195
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:05,045
I wonder if this is the last time we'll meet.

196
00:14:07,547 --> 00:14:10,050
Thank you so far.

197
00:14:15,055 --> 00:14:20,994
(Manami) Love may turn into violence.

198
00:14:21,061 --> 00:14:27,067
But it also gives me the strength to live.

199
00:14:29,069 --> 00:14:34,507
Love has that kind of power.

200
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:39,446
>> Manami-chan...

201
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,516
(Manami) I'll hear the counterargument next time.

202
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:47,587
Don't think you can apologize and get away with it.

203
00:14:49,589 --> 00:14:51,591
>>Thank you...

204
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:02,369
(Kiyosumi) Hey, you're not doing that.

205
00:15:02,435 --> 00:15:05,372
(Manami) That's why I did it. >> Huh!?

206
00:15:05,438 --> 00:15:07,941
(Manami) It's there, right? >> What...｡

207
00:15:10,443 --> 00:15:15,382
Why were you able to write the report so quickly?

208
00:15:15,448 --> 00:15:19,886
(Manami) Lately, all I have to do is work.

209
00:15:19,953 --> 00:15:21,888
>> Who are you? Bring back Tanizaki.

210
00:15:21,955 --> 00:15:24,891
Bring back that stupid Tanizaki! Hehehehe~

211
00:15:24,958 --> 00:15:27,394
What is this? (Manami) …Hmph.

212
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:29,896
>>What, “Hmph”? Hey! I'm curious.

213
00:15:29,963 --> 00:15:32,399
If you have something to say, say it confidently... (Manami) Ah!

214
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:34,401
>> Hey...｡

215
00:15:34,467 --> 00:15:37,904
(Iori's voice) Well, I haven't met my love and the others.

216
00:15:37,971 --> 00:15:39,906
(Manami) Yeah...｡

217
00:15:39,973 --> 00:15:44,411
I don't know what kind of face I should make when I meet you.

218
00:15:44,477 --> 00:15:46,913
>>Aren't we going to meet again?

219
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:51,985
(Manami) Hmm... I want to meet you though.

220
00:15:53,486 --> 00:15:56,923
>> Well then, it's okay, it's your own happiness →

221
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:58,925
If you decide for yourself.

222
00:15:58,992 --> 00:16:00,927
(Manami) But in the end →

223
00:16:00,994 --> 00:16:04,998
This way of life hurt many people.

224
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:09,436
I wonder if I can continue...

225
00:16:11,938 --> 00:16:16,376
>> That's for them to decide, right?

226
00:16:16,443 --> 00:16:20,380
I may have hurt a lot of people →

227
00:16:20,447 --> 00:16:24,384
Didn't it make you happy too? Just in case.

228
00:16:24,451 --> 00:16:27,887
(Manami) Yeah, well, that's my intention.

229
00:16:27,954 --> 00:16:30,890
>> Well, you have to take responsibility for yourself. (Manami) Eh, that's cold.

230
00:16:30,957 --> 00:16:34,394
>> It's natural, you're an adult now.

231
00:16:34,461 --> 00:16:37,897
There's no doubt that it's a strange way to live.

232
00:16:37,964 --> 00:16:41,901
(Manami) Hmm! But after all, 10 years later →

233
00:16:41,968 --> 00:16:45,405
This my love style might become popular.

234
00:16:45,472 --> 00:16:48,041
>> No, I don't think so. Just one person per country is enough.

235
00:16:48,108 --> 00:16:51,044
If it keeps going around, it's going to become an international problem.

236
00:16:51,111 --> 00:16:54,047
what? Do you want to become an Earth crusher?

237
00:16:54,114 --> 00:16:57,550
(Manami) Huh? Avengers? >> It's the enemy side, no matter how you think about it.

238
00:16:57,617 --> 00:17:00,053
(Manami) Haha...｡

239
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:11,998
♪～

240
00:17:12,065 --> 00:17:15,502
>>Don't pour it yourself.

241
00:17:15,568 --> 00:17:20,573
Since she's not here anymore, please help me.

242
00:17:22,575 --> 00:17:24,511
(Manami) Yeah...｡

243
00:17:24,577 --> 00:17:43,530
♪～

244
00:17:43,596 --> 00:17:47,534
(Manami) Yeah... this is what I thought →

245
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:51,037
It's not tasty.

246
00:17:51,104 --> 00:17:54,107
>> I've done it before.

247
00:17:56,109 --> 00:18:01,548
(Manami) Seriously... I can't taste it.

248
00:18:01,614 --> 00:18:03,550
What is this?

249
00:18:03,616 --> 00:18:07,554
(Sound of sipping)

250
00:18:11,057 --> 00:18:15,495
>> It's true... it's the worst.

251
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:17,997
It's only natural.

252
00:18:18,064 --> 00:18:23,002
(Manami) It's true, it's only natural.

253
00:18:23,069 --> 00:18:25,505
(Sound of sipping)

254
00:18:25,572 --> 00:18:28,575
>>Let's drink! (Manami) Yes.

255
00:18:32,579 --> 00:18:35,515
(Kiryu) No, no, Mr. Kiyosumi's hearing →

256
00:18:35,582 --> 00:18:38,017
It's still an exaggeration.

257
00:18:38,084 --> 00:18:40,587
It's so nostalgic.

258
00:18:47,594 --> 00:18:50,029
Looks like you're doing well.

259
00:18:50,096 --> 00:18:53,533
(Manami) I'm in a rather bad mood right now.

260
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:57,036
>> Being able to grump properly is proof that you are healthy.

261
00:18:57,103 --> 00:19:00,540
(Manami) What do you think?

262
00:19:00,607 --> 00:19:03,543
>> It's great that everyone seems to be doing well. (Manami) Yeah.

263
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:06,479
>>One person is sweltering upstairs.

264
00:19:06,546 --> 00:19:09,048
Hard work after a long time! That's it.

265
00:19:15,054 --> 00:19:17,056
(Manami) Huh…｡

266
00:19:22,061 --> 00:19:24,564
(Manami) Welcome back.

267
00:19:28,067 --> 00:19:31,504
(Kuroiwa) We apologize for the inconvenience.

268
00:19:31,571 --> 00:19:36,509
(Manami) No, I'm sorry for everything.

269
00:19:36,576 --> 00:19:40,513
(Kuroiwa) No, I'm glad it was resolved.

270
00:19:41,481 --> 00:19:43,850
Ah, isn't it good?

271
00:19:43,917 --> 00:19:46,352
(Manami) I'm glad it was good.

272
00:19:46,419 --> 00:19:49,923
(Kuroiwa) But please don't overdo it.

273
00:19:51,925 --> 00:19:54,928
(Manami) Even if someone who has just been discharged from the hospital tells you that.

274
00:19:59,432 --> 00:20:04,938
(Manami) You are such a kind detective.

275
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:12,312
(Manami) What happened?

276
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:15,315
(Kuroiwa) I love you, Manami-san.

277
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:17,817
(Manami) Wait, what are you talking about?

278
00:20:17,884 --> 00:20:20,320
Is there anyone to confess at the Metropolitan Police Department?

279
00:20:20,386 --> 00:20:22,322
Oh, are you lazy on vacation?

280
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:25,325
(Kuroiwa) Ah, but before →

281
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:28,328
I meant that I only wanted you to look at me.→

282
00:20:28,394 --> 00:20:32,332
Now, if you can just laugh at something→

283
00:20:32,398 --> 00:20:36,336
I love that kind of thing.

284
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:39,339
♪～

285
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:42,842
(Manami) No matter how many times I push you away, you'll never follow me.

286
00:20:42,909 --> 00:20:44,911
(Kuroiwa) Sorry.

287
00:20:46,412 --> 00:20:50,850
(Manami) No, I'm sorry.

288
00:20:50,917 --> 00:20:53,152
Get involved in a strange incident →

289
00:20:53,219 --> 00:20:55,655
Call me to a pension or temple →

290
00:20:55,722 --> 00:20:59,158
Finally, I was sent to the hospital.

291
00:20:59,225 --> 00:21:01,160
(Kuroiwa) Certainly.

292
00:21:01,227 --> 00:21:04,230
What kind of hara is it?

293
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:09,102
(Manami) Still, I followed you.

294
00:21:09,168 --> 00:21:12,171
He followed me.

295
00:21:15,174 --> 00:21:17,610
(Manami) Maybe →

296
00:21:17,677 --> 00:21:21,114
There is no one who cares about me as much as Kuroiwa-kun →

297
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:24,117
I guess there isn't one.

298
00:21:24,183 --> 00:21:28,621
(Kuroiwa) Yes, probably so.

299
00:21:28,688 --> 00:21:31,624
(Manami) That's why...

300
00:21:31,691 --> 00:21:36,629
♪～

301
00:21:36,696 --> 00:21:39,632
(Manami) Will you be my friend?

302
00:21:39,699 --> 00:21:42,635
(Kuroiwa) Friends? (Manami) No, this doesn't happen very often!

303
00:21:42,702 --> 00:21:45,138
A 100% pure male friend.

304
00:21:45,204 --> 00:21:47,640
(Kuroiwa) Is that what you mean by being so proud?

305
00:21:47,707 --> 00:21:51,144
(Manami) When you get to this point, you're usually in love.

306
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:55,148
(Kuroiwa) Huh... I guess I should be happy.

307
00:21:55,214 --> 00:21:59,652
(Manami) I'll take great care of you~｡

308
00:21:59,719 --> 00:22:03,156
(Kuroiwa) Wow... something →

309
00:22:03,222 --> 00:22:06,092
There is a part of me that is just a little happy.

310
00:22:06,159 --> 00:22:08,094
(Manami) Ahaha. (Kuroiwa) What is this...?

311
00:22:08,161 --> 00:22:12,098
(Manami) That's right, you can just be happy.

312
00:22:12,165 --> 00:22:14,100
(Kuroiwa) Let's go for the promised meal.

313
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:16,102
Please celebrate your recovery.

314
00:22:16,169 --> 00:22:17,603
(Manami) Next time.

315
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:20,106
There's something a little different today.

316
00:22:20,173 --> 00:22:23,109
(Kuroiwa) Huh... I can't really understand or empathize with that.

317
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:25,111
You're doing well, really.

318
00:22:25,178 --> 00:22:27,613
(Manami) Hmm.

319
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:31,117
I can't do this all the time.

320
00:22:31,184 --> 00:22:35,621
♪～

321
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:40,126
(Manami) There are too many people to fall in love with in this world!

322
00:22:40,193 --> 00:22:44,197
♪～
